  "informal_statement": "For an arithmetic sequence starting at a with common difference d, twice the sum of the first n terms equals n * (2a + (n-1)*d) -- the general arithmetic-series formula.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Induction on n: the base case n = 0 is the empty sum equalling 0 * (2a + (-1)*d) = 0. In the successor step, split off the last term a + n*d with Finset.sum_range_succ, distribute the *2 via add_mul, apply the inductive hypothesis, then push_cast (to align the ℕ->ℤ casts of n and n+1) and ring close the resulting polynomial identity.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem arith_seq_sum (a d : ℤ) (n : ℕ) : (∑ i ∈ Finset.range n, (a + (i : ℤ) * d)) * 2 = (n : ℤ) * (2 * a + ((n : ℤ) - 1) * d)",
