  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode b6ef7a97), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Generalizes three of the domain's existing closed-form sum packets into a single reusable lemma: gauss_sum is the a=0, d=1 case; sum_odds is a=1, d=2; sum_evens is a=2, d=2. Stated over ℤ (rather than ℕ) so (n-1) can go negative at n=0 without truncation, matching the domain's established pattern (geom_series_sum_induction, telescoping_sum) of picking an ordered ring where the natural algebra holds cleanly.",
